{"author":{"id":"1e0a6ff3e01313072cf7b3803c158c22d01a37717237fe198e814e781752b172"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1781888628,"nonce":"DTEvzVhJ9YqWzCph1v2lTL8w0S0=","title":"test_clear_target_branch flakes on py3.12 under full-suite load (Textual Footer NoMatches)","message":"## Summary\n\n`src/tests/test_tui_tracking.py::TestTargetBranch::test_clear_target_branch`\nintermittently fails on Python 3.12 with:\n\n    textual.css.query.NoMatches: No nodes match 'Footer' on Screen(id='_default')\n\n## Repro profile\n\n- **Python 3.12 only** — 3.11, 3.13, 3.14 all clean.\n- **Full-suite load only** — 0/40 failures when the test runs in isolation;\n  surfaces at roughly ~1 failure per several full `pytest src/tests/` runs.\n- First observed 2026-06-19 during `ci-matrix.sh` validation of the\n  feature/checkout-cwd-race branch (4edac7d).  Pre-existing; completely\n  unrelated to those changes.\n\n## Root cause hypothesis\n\nThe Textual `Footer` widget is not yet mounted when `query_one(Footer)` is\ncalled during a screen transition.  The same mount-before-query race\n(`await self.mount(..., before=self.query_one(Footer))`) exists in the\nreview_tui mount helpers; something similar fires in this test's teardown or\ntarget-branch-clear path.\n\nPython 3.12's thread scheduling appears to expose the window more readily\nthan other versions.\n\n## Suggested fix\n\nEither:\n1. Add a small `await self.app.workers.wait_for_complete()` / `settle()` call\n   before any `query_one(Footer)` lookup during screen transitions, or\n2. Make the querying code tolerate Footer's absence mid-transition (guard with\n   `query(Footer).first()` and bail if empty).\n\n## Triage notes\n\nSingle 3.12 failure on this test in a CI/matrix run = known flake, not a\nregression.  Re-run to confirm before blocking a merge.","files":null}]}